CustomObject.name: CustomObject
CustomObject.description: Represents a custom object that stores data unique to your organization. Includes access to the associated CustomObject object and related fields in Salesforce Metadata API.

CustomHelpId.description: The control that contains the help content if this custom object has customized help content.

Description.description: The object’s description. This can be useful to describe the reason for creating the object or its intended use.

DeveloperName.description: The developer’s internal name for the custom object. For example, the internal name for the custom object CO__c is CO.

ExternalName.description: Maps to a table in the external data source. If you created the external object using Validate and Sync for the data source, this name is automatically created.

ExternalRepository.description: Maps to a table in the external data source. If you created the external object using Validate and Sync for the data source, this name is automatically created; do not modify it.

Language.description: The language of the action. Valid values are: Chinese (Simplified): zh_CN Chinese (Traditional): zh_TW Danish: da Dutch: nl_NL English: en_US Finnish: fi French: fr German: de Italian: it Japanese: ja Korean: ko Norwegian: no Portuguese (Brazil): pt_BR Russian: ru Spanish: es Spanish (Mexico): es_MX Spanish (Mexico) defaults to Spanish for customer-defined translations. Swedish: sv Thai: th The Salesforce user interface is fully translated to Thai, but Help is in English.

ManageableState.description: Indicates the manageable state of the specified component that is contained in a package: beta deleted deprecated deprecatedEditable installed installedEditable released unmanaged

NamespacePrefix.description: The namespace of the package of which the custom object is a part.

SharingModel.description: The sharing model. Values are: Edit ControlledByparent None Read
